{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"266124c7-e36d-4a24-bb67-e68faeb158aa","content":"Here's what you need to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.runner.mtp` package instead:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"*\" />\n   ```\n   Use a version compatible with xunit 2.9.3 (check [NuGet](https://www.nuget.org/packages/xunit.runner.mtp) for the latest).\n\n3. **Add** this property to your `.csproj` (in a `<PropertyGroup>`):\n   ```xml\n   <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   ```\n   This enables `dotnet test` integration with MTP.\n\n4. **Optionally add**:\n   ```xml\n   <EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>\n   ```\n   if you want built-in code coverage support.\n\n5. **Run** `dotnet test` to verify everything works.\n\nYour test code itself doesn't need to change — only the runner infrastructure is swapped.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"57540e26-5aae-45d0-920c-66ef23080418","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration.","outputTokens":363,"requestId":"A03C:E8763:BCFBBC:DCFFAC:69FE84F3"},"id":"f9d6c3b2-276a-444d-af4c-31ace2d2b8ac","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:51:12.230Z","parentId":"b3b6dac6-bde9-4e9d-baa1-c47de897ea38"}
